Detailed Description

A Request that makes a message of a route that optinally can be sent as an email.

Create a RouteMessageRequest.

Parameters:
reqID unique request ID.
routeID The ID of the route, used to update the valid time of the route in the database, set to 0 if not to update.
routeCreateTime The creation time of the route, used to update the valid time of the route in the database, set to 0 if not to update.
lang The desired language of the message.
routePack The RouteReplyPacket with the route.
expand The ExpandRouteReplyPacket with the route.
exp The ExpandItemID with the RouteItems stored, may be NULL then a new one is created from expand.
routeOverviewWidth The width of the overview image.
routeOverviewHeight The height of the overview image.
routeTurnWidth The width of the turn images.
routeTurnHeight The height of the turn images.
originString String describing the origin, like STOCKHOLM-BROMMA AIRPORT
originLocationString String describing the origin's location, like Alvik.
destinationString String describing the destination, like Gustavslundsvgen Alvik.
destinationLocationString String describing the destination's location, like Alvik.
routeVehicle The type of vehicle at the start of the route.
topReq Pointer to valid TopRegionRequest with data
makeImages If the message should contain the images refered to in the route.
makeLink If a link to a webpage containing the html version of the message.
realMapURLS If map image urls should be real ones that can be sent to a [XML|HTTP]Server.
includeLandmarks If landmarks should be show in route description, default true.
useNavTurnBoundingBox If use alternative getNavCrossingMC2BoundingBox method for making turn bboxes, default false, requires coordinates in expanded route.
exportMap If return ExportGfxFeatureMap data and not image map data, default false.
onlyOverview If make a route message with only overview image.
contentType The type of message wanted.
turnImageType The type of route turn images to use.
arrowType The type of turn arrow to draw, default NOT_USED.
maxMessageSize The maximum size of a message, default MAX_UINT32.
sendEmail If the message should be sent as an email.
toMailAdr The receipitent of the email, used if sendEmail.
fromMailAdr The sender of the email, used if sendEmail.
subject The subject of the email, used if sendEmail.
signature The signuture, text last, of the email.
defaultFormat The default format of the images. Default PNG.
user The user doing the request, default NULL.
contentLocation If to add Content-Location or Content-ID, default Content-ID.
mapSetting The defaultMapSetting to use. Default STD.
imageSettings The ImageSettings to use, default NULL.
messageStartFmt Format string where: "%DIRECTIONS%", "%FROM%", "%TO%", "%ORIGINSTRING%","%DESTINATIONSTRING%", "%ORIGINLOCATIONSTRING%", "%DESTINATIONLOCATIONSTRING%", "%ROUTEOVERVIEW_URI%","%ROUTEOVERVIEW_WIDTH%", "%ROUTEOVERVIEW_HEIGHT%", "%ROUTEOVERVIEW_ALT%", "%ROUTE_INFO%", "%VEHICLE%, "ROUTE_VEHICLE%", "%TOTAL_DISTANCE%","%ROUTE_TOTAL_DISTANCE%", "%TOTAL_TIME%", "%ROUTE_TOTAL_TIME%" are replaced by actual strings (use without citations).
messageRestartFmt Format string where: "%DIRECTIONS%", "%FROM%", "%TO%", "%ORIGINSTRING%","%DESTINATIONSTRING%", "%ORIGINLOCATIONSTRING%", "%DESTINATIONLOCATIONSTRING%", "%ROUTEOVERVIEW_URI%","%ROUTEOVERVIEW_WIDTH%", "%ROUTEOVERVIEW_HEIGHT%", "%ROUTEOVERVIEW_ALT%", "%ROUTE_INFO%", "%VEHICLE%, "ROUTE_VEHICLE%", "%TOTAL_DISTANCE%","%ROUTE_TOTAL_DISTANCE%", "%TOTAL_TIME%", "%ROUTE_TOTAL_TIME%" are replaced by actual strings (use without citations).
messageRouteTurnFmt Formart string where: "%ROUTE_DESCRIPTION%", "%ROUTE_TURN_URI%", "%ROUTE_TURN_WIDTH%", "%ROUTE_TURN_HEIGHT%" "%ROUTE_TURN_ALT%", "%ROUTE_PRE_LANDMARKS%", "%ROUTE_POST_LANDMARKS%" are replaced by actual strings (use without citations).
messageRoutePreTurnLandmarkFmt Format string used for pre turn landmarks in messageRouteTurnFmt. "%ROUTE_LANDMARK_DESCRIPTION%".
messageRoutePostTurnLandmarkFmt Format string used for post turn landmarks in messageRouteTurnFmt. "%ROUTE_LANDMARK_DESCRIPTION%".
messageEndFmt Formart string where: "%SIGNATURE%" is replaced by actual string (use without citations).
nbrMessageResources The number of resources that are static in the message.
messageResourcesURI The URI of the messageresources.
messageResourcesBuffLength The length of the resources in messageResourcesBuff.
messageResourcesBuff The raw bytes the the messageResources.
navigatorCrossingMaps If this request is only used for getting crossingmaps for the navigator (exportscaleable gfxfeaturemaps). This means that the result is not valid for anything else than just to use as crossing maps.
mapSettings By submitting this parameter, the information in mapSetting and imageSettings is overridden. Ie. if you want to specify more detailed mapsettings then you can do by those two parameters. Note however, if realMapURLs is true, then the mapURLs will reflect the information in mapSetting and imageSettings, and not the information from this parameter.
